  "prompt": "What universities does Concert Pharmaceuticals recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Concert Pharmaceuticals, like many biopharmaceutical companies, tends to recruit new graduates from universities with strong programs in relevant fields. While specific universities may not be consistently listed, they likely look for candidates from institutions known for their strengths in pharmaceutical sciences, biology, chemistry, biotechnology, and related disciplines. They typically seek graduates with majors such as:\n\n1. Pharmaceutical Sciences\n2. Chemistry\n3. Biology\n4. Biochemistry\n5. Biotechnology\n6. Pharmacology\n7. Chemical Engineering\n\nConcert Pharmaceuticals may also partner with universities that have dedicated research programs or industry connections in these areas. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's a good idea to visit the careers section of Concert Pharmaceuticals' website or reach out directly to their HR department to inquire about their recruitment practices. Networking at industry conferences, career fairs, and through university career services can also provide insights into their recruiting preferences.",
